docs.abstract: A federal judge has dismissed a suit brought by the city that would have forced fossil fuel companies to pay for some costs of climate change.
docs.snippet: A federal judge has dismissed a suit brought by the city that would have forced fossil fuel companies to pay for some costs of climate change.
docs.lead_paragraph: A federal judge has rejected New York City’s lawsuit to make fossil fuel companies help pay the costs of dealing with climate change.

headline.main: Judge Throws Out New York Climate Lawsuit

docs.abstract: The state oil company was under pressure after ConocoPhillips, which had won an arbitration ruling in a decade-long fight, seized cargoes and terminals to force compliance.
docs.snippet: The state oil company was under pressure after ConocoPhillips, which had won an arbitration ruling in a decade-long fight, seized cargoes and terminals to force compliance.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — More than a decade ago, Venezuela seized several oil projects from the American oil company ConocoPhillips without compensation. Now, under pressure after ConocoPhillips carried out its own seizures, the Venezuelans are going to make amends.

headline.main: Venezuela Agrees to Pay $2 Billion Over Seizure of Oil Projects
headline.print_headline: Venezuela to Pay ConocoPhillips $2 Billion for Seizing Oil Projects

docs.abstract: As the Treasury Department prepared to enact the 2017 Republican tax overhaul, corporate lobbyists swarmed — and won big.
docs.snippet: As the Treasury Department prepared to enact the 2017 Republican tax overhaul, corporate lobbyists swarmed — and won big.
docs.lead_paragraph: The overhaul of the federal tax law in 2017 was the signature legislative achievement of Donald J. Trump’s presidency.

headline.main: How Big Companies Won New Tax Breaks From the Trump Administration
headline.print_headline: Business Got Big Tax Cut; Lobbyists Made It Bigger

byline.original: By Jesse Drucker and Jim Tankersley

docs.abstract: An arbitration panel sided with the company 11 years after Hugo Chávez expropriated several of its oil projects. Now the problem is trying to collect.
docs.snippet: An arbitration panel sided with the company 11 years after Hugo Chávez expropriated several of its oil projects. Now the problem is trying to collect.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — ConocoPhillips won a ruling on Wednesday that says it is entitled to more than $2 billion from Venezuela’s state oil company over the country’s expropriation of several oil projects more than a decade ago.

headline.main: ConocoPhillips Wins $2 Billion Ruling Over Venezuelan Seizure
headline.print_headline: Panel Awards Energy Firm $2 Billion From Venezuela
